face doesn't fit
Homonym Number:
Word Class: phrase
Sense Number:
Definition:
Origin:
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: Can't identify positively the original clause which provoked this description but the nearest is the clause in the State Sector Act of 1988 which refers to the dismissal of a Chief Executive: The [Commissioner] may, with the agreement of the Governor-General in Council, for just cause or excuse, remove the Chief Executive of a Department from office. [<i>NZ Statutes</i>, 1988, 1(20)  244 or <i>Revised Statutes</i>. 33 (1995) : 73.]
